div.div: DomainContext provides a supervisor factory implementation backed by a single local actor. The main purpose of the supervisor factory is to create supervisors in the same context.

div.div: Entity supervisors are backed by a local actor per entity type. Entity supervisors decide where entities are created based on the domain context implementation. Entities are created using the factory for that entity type.Â

div.div: Command messages are sent to the entity supervisor. The entity supervisor uses id resolution to obtain the entity id from the message and can use this information to decide where to get or create the entity actor. The message is forwarded to the entity actor.
